	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />In case anyone posts source-codes of their game in public-domain, then it is possible to take part of their codes and use them in your game too. And then you can fix them to do how you like it to do. (I don't know how many such public-domain codes people are making, although I think some of the NES games programmed in C are in public domain; you should look to see if it is.)

		

		</td>
